import React from 'react'

const Datatable = () => {
  return (
    <div className='datatable'>Java Introduction
    What is Java?
    Java is a popular programming language, born in 1995.
    It is owned by Oracle, and more than 3 billion devices run Java.
    It is good at:
    •	Mobile applications (especially Android apps)
    •	Desktop applications
    •	Web applications
    •	Web servers and application servers
    •	Games
    •	Database connection
    The advantages of Java:
    •	Java works on all kinds of platforms (Windows, Mac, Linux, Raspberry Pi, etc.)
    •	It is one of the most used programming languages among the developers
    •	Compared with other languages, it is easier to learn and simpler to use
    •	It is open-source and free
    •	It is secure, fast and strong
    •	It has a large community support
    •	Java is an object-oriented language which show the program structure clearly and support the code to be reused, lowering costs
    Example Java program 
    // create a burger maker called chef 
    BurgerMaker chef = new BurgerMaker(); 
    // tell chef to add bottom bun 
    chef.addBottomBun(); 
    // tell chef to add patty 
    chef.addPatty();

    // tell chef to add cheese 
    chef.addCheese(); 
    // tell chef to add top bun 
    chef.addTopBun(); 
    // tell chef to set name as Cheeseburger 
    chef.setName("Cheeseburger"); 
    // tell chef to set price at 2.00 
    chef.setPrice(2.00);
    Java programs •
     For the moment, 
    – one or more .java files
     • each defines a Java class (with the same name as the file)
     • at least one should have a main method 
    – possibly one or more .jar archives 
    • containing pre-defined code 

    To make the program do its work 
    – compile the program
     • Check & translate into something the machine can understand
     – execute it


    </div>
  )
}

export default Datatable
